20some%20tech%20leaders%20say%20there%20is%20no%20wall.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20prompted%20a%20debate%20over%20how%20companies%20can%20overcome%20AI%20bottlenecks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spoke%20to%2012%20people%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20AI%20boom%20to%20find%20out%20the%20path%20forward.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESilicon%20Valley%20leaders%20all-in%20on%20the%20artificial%20intelligence%20boom%20have%20a%20message%20for%20critics%3A%20their%20technology%20has%20not%20hit%20a%20wall.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20fierce%20debate%20over%20whether%20improvements%20in%20AI%20models%20have%20hit%20their%20limit%20has%20taken%20hold%20in%20recent%20weeks%2C%20forcing%20several%20CEOs%20to%20respond.%20OpenAI%20boss%20Sam%20Altman%20was%20among%20the%20first%20to%20speak%20out%2C%20posting%20on%20X%20this%20month%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-ai-wall-slowdown-openai-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20no%20wall.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDario%20Amodei%2C%20CEO%20of%20rival%20firm%20Anthropic%2C%20and%20Jensen%20Huang%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Nvidia%2C%20have%20also%20disputed%20reports%20that%20AI%20%3C%2Fspan%3Eprogress%20has%20slowed.%20Others%2C%20including%20Marc%20Andreessen%2C%20say%20AI%20models%20aren't%20getting%20noticeably%20better%20and%20are%20all%20converging%20to%20perform%20at%20roughly%20similar%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20a%20trillion-dollar%20question%20for%20the%20tech%20industry.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20If%20tried-and-tested%20AI%20model%20training%20methods%20are%20providing%20diminishing%20returns%2C%20it%20could%20undermine%20the%20core%20reason%20for%20an%20unprecedented%20investment%20cycle%20that's%20funding%20new%20startups%2C%20products%2C%20and%20data%20centers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-nuclear-power-ai-data-centers-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erekindling%20idled%20nuclear%20power%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spoke%20to%2012%20people%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20AI%20industry%2C%20including%20startup%20founders%2C%20investors%2C%20and%20current%20and%20former%20insiders%20at%20Google%20DeepMind%20and%20OpenAI%2C%20about%20the%20challenges%20and%20opportunities%20ahead%20in%20the%20quest%20for%20superintelligent%20AI.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETogether%2C%20they%20said%20that%20tapping%20into%20new%20types%20of%20data%2C%20building%20reasoning%20into%20systems%2C%20and%20creating%20smaller%20but%20more%20specialized%20models%20are%20some%20of%20the%20ways%20to%20keep%20the%20wheels%20of%20AI%20progress%20turning.%3Cspan%3E%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a048b8ba-c38e-4a70-be6a-16ff8e565a28%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20pre-training%20dilemma%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20point%20to%20two%20key%20blocks%20that%20companies%20may%20encounter%20in%20an%20early%20phase%20of%20AI%20development%2C%20known%20as%20pre-training.%20The%20first%20is%20access%20to%20computing%20power.%20More%20specifically%2C%20this%20means%20getting%20hold%20of%20specialist%20chips%20called%20GPUs.%20It's%20a%20market%20dominated%20by%20Santa%20Clara-based%20chip%20giant%20Nvidia%2C%20which%20has%20battled%20with%20supply%20constraints%20in%20the%20face%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-ceo-jensen-huang-product-shortages-making-customers-emotional-tense-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enonstop%20demand%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20%2450%20million%20to%20spend%20on%20GPUs%20but%20you're%20on%20the%20bottom%20of%20Nvidia's%20list%20%E2%80%94%20we%20don't%20have%20enough%20kimchi%20to%20throw%20at%20this%2C%20and%20it%20will%20take%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Henri%20Tilloy%2C%20partner%20at%20French%20VC%20firm%20Singular.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jensen%20Huang%20wih%20Nvidia%20hardware%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66cf1d7b43b5e59d16b5e046%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJensen%20Huang's%20Nvidia%20has%20become%20the%20world's%20most%20valuable%20company%20off%20the%20back%20of%20the%20AI%20boom.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Sullivan%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20another%20supply%20problem%2C%20too%3A%20training%20data.%20AI%20companies%20have%20run%20into%20limits%20on%20the%20quantity%20of%20public%20data%20they%20can%20secure%20to%20feed%20into%20their%20large%20language%20models%2C%20or%20LLMs%2C%20in%20pre-training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20phase%20involves%20training%20an%20LLM%20on%20a%20vast%20corpus%20of%20data%2C%20typically%20scraped%20from%20the%20internet%2C%20and%20then%20processed%20by%20GPUs.%20That%20information%20is%20then%20broken%20down%20into%20%26quot%3Btokens%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20form%20the%20fundamental%20units%20of%20data%20processed%20by%20a%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20throwing%20more%20data%20and%20GPUs%20at%20a%20model%20has%20reliably%20produced%20smarter%20models%20year%20after%20year%2C%20companies%20have%20been%20exhausting%20the%20supply%20of%20publicly%20available%20data%20on%20the%20internet.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fepoch.ai%2Fblog%2Fwill-we-run-out-of-data-limits-of-llm-scaling-based-on-human-generated-data%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResearch%20firm%20Epoch%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20predicts%20usable%20textual%20data%20could%20be%20squeezed%20dry%20by%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20internet%20is%20only%20so%20large%2C%26quot%3B%20Matthew%20Zeiler%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Clarifai%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2270a25fe2-06df-41b5-b30d-6fce0d3f71b3%5C%22%3EMultimodal%20and%20private%20data%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEric%20Landau%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20data%20startup%20Encord%2C%20said%20that%20this%20is%20where%20other%20data%20sources%20will%20offer%20a%20path%20forward%20in%20the%20scramble%20to%20overcome%20the%20bottleneck%20in%20public%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20example%20is%20multimodal%20data%2C%20which%20involves%20feeding%20AI%20systems%20visual%20and%20audio%20sources%20of%20information%2C%20such%20as%20photos%20or%20podcast%20recordings.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20one%20part%20of%20the%20picture%2C%26quot%3B%20Landau%20said.%20%26quot%3BJust%20adding%20more%20modalities%20of%20data.%26quot%3B%20AI%20labs%20have%20already%20started%20using%20multimodal%20data%20as%20a%20tool%2C%20but%20Landau%20says%20it%20remains%20%26quot%3Bvery%20underutilized.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESharon%20Zhou%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20LLM%20platform%20Lamini%2C%20sees%20another%20vastly%20untapped%20area%3A%20private%20data.%20Companies%20have%20been%20securing%20licensing%20agreements%20with%20publishers%20to%20gain%20access%20to%20their%20vast%20troves%20of%20information.%20OpenAI%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20has%20struck%20partnerships%20with%20organizations%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Findex%2Fa-content-and-product-partnership-with-vox-media%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVox%20Media%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Findex%2Fapi-partnership-with-stack-overflow%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStack%20Overflow%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20Q%26amp%3BA%20platform%20for%20developers%2C%20to%20bring%20copyrighted%20data%20into%20their%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20not%20even%20close%20to%20using%20all%20of%20the%20private%20data%20in%20the%20world%20to%20supplement%20the%20data%20we%20need%20for%20pre-training%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhou%20said.%20%26quot%3BFrom%20work%20with%20our%20enterprise%20and%20even%20startup%20customers%2C%20there's%20a%20lot%20more%20signal%20in%20that%20data%20that%20is%20very%20useful%20for%20these%20models%20to%20capture.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c4e6549f-f46a-4762-9364-b4f309059a33%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20data%20quality%20problem%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20great%20deal%20of%20research%20effort%20is%20now%20focused%20on%20enhancing%20the%20quality%20of%20data%20that%20an%20LLM%20is%20trained%20on%20rather%20than%20just%20the%20quantity.%20Researchers%20could%20previously%20afford%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20lazy%20about%20the%20data%26quot%3B%20in%20pre-training%2C%20Zhou%20said%2C%20by%20just%20chucking%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20at%20a%20model%20to%20see%20what%20stuck.%20%26quot%3BThis%20isn't%20totally%20true%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20solution%20that%20companies%20are%20exploring%20is%20synthetic%20data%2C%20an%20artificial%20form%20of%20data%20generated%20by%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Daniele%20Panfilo%2C%20CEO%20of%20startup%20Aindo%20AI%2C%20synthetic%20data%20can%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bpowerful%20tool%20to%20improve%20data%20quality%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20can%20%26quot%3Bhelp%20researchers%20construct%20datasets%20that%20meet%20their%20exact%20information%20needs.%26quot%3B%20This%20is%20particularly%20useful%20in%20a%20phase%20of%20AI%20development%20known%20as%20post-training%2C%20where%20techniques%20such%20as%20fine-tuning%20can%20be%20used%20to%20give%20a%20pre-trained%20model%20a%20smaller%20dataset%20that%20has%20been%20carefully%20crafted%20with%20specific%20domain%20expertise%2C%20such%20as%20law%20or%20medicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20former%20employee%20at%20Google%20DeepMind%2C%20the%20search%20giant's%20AI%20lab%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20%26quot%3BGemini%20has%20shifted%20its%20strategy%26quot%3B%20from%20going%20bigger%20to%20more%20efficient.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20they've%20realized%20that%20it%20is%20actually%20very%20expensive%20to%20serve%20such%20large%20models%2C%20and%20it%20is%20better%20to%20specialize%20them%20for%20various%20tasks%20through%20better%20post-training%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222854%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google%20i%2Fo%20event%20Sundar%20Pichai%20Gemini%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66439ab8b4abc992e8c95e2a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221492%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle%20launched%20Gemini%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Bard%2C%20in%202023.%3Cp%3EGoogle%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20theory%2C%20synthetic%20data%20offers%20a%20useful%20way%20to%20hone%20a%20model's%20knowledge%20and%20make%20it%20smaller%20and%20more%20efficient.%20In%20practice%2C%20there's%20no%20full%20consensus%20on%20how%20effective%20synthetic%20data%20can%20be%20in%20making%20models%20smarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20discovered%20this%20year%20with%20our%20synthetic%20data%2C%20called%20Cosmopedia%2C%20is%20that%20it%20can%20help%20for%20some%20things%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20the%20silver%20bullet%20that's%20going%20to%20solve%20our%20data%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20Thomas%20Wolf%2C%20cofounder%20and%20chief%20science%20officer%20at%20open-source%20platform%20Hugging%20Face%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Frankle%2C%20the%20chief%20AI%20scientist%20at%20Databricks%2C%20said%20there's%20no%20%26quot%3Bfree%20lunch%20%26quot%3B%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20synthetic%20data%20and%20emphasized%20the%20need%20for%20human%20oversight.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20have%20any%20human%20insight%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20have%20any%20process%20of%20filtering%20and%20choosing%20which%20synthetic%20data%20is%20most%20relevant%2C%20then%20all%20the%20model%20is%20doing%20is%20reproducing%20its%20own%20behavior%20because%20that's%20what%20the%20model%20is%20intended%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConcerns%20around%20synthetic%20data%20came%20to%20a%20head%20after%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dbe468ee8ce72a81899f985f5f8550abdd05c3e150925e5b87d82d02e5a0c7498%26postID%3D673df6dfcb042e5dec0da49a%26postSlug%3Dgenerative-ai-wall-scaling-laws-training-data-chatgpt-gemini-claude-2024-11%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41586-024-07566-y%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%20published%20in%20July%20in%20the%20journal%20Nature%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20there%20was%20a%20risk%20of%20%26quot%3Bmodel%20collapse%26quot%3B%20with%20%26quot%3Bindiscriminate%20use%26quot%3B%20of%20synthetic%20data.%20The%20message%20was%20to%20tread%20carefully.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2214e4ae2a-21c9-44ad-8af9-59f0174692a7%5C%22%3EBuilding%20a%20reasoning%20machine%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20simply%20focusing%20on%20the%20training%20portion%20won't%20cut%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20OpenAI%20chief%20scientist%20and%20Safe%20Superintelligence%20cofounder%20Ilya%20Sutskever%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Ftechnology%2Fartificial-intelligence%2Fopenai-rivals-seek-new-path-smarter-ai-current-methods-hit-limitations-2024-11-11%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Reuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20month%20that%20results%20from%20scaling%20models%20in%20pre-training%20had%20plateaued%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Beveryone%20is%20looking%20for%20the%20next%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20%26quot%3Bnext%20thing%26quot%3B%20looks%20to%20be%20reasoning.%20Industry%20attention%20has%20increasingly%20turned%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-players-startups-ai-inference-driving-prices-down-cheap-workload-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earea%20of%20AI%20known%20as%20inference%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20focuses%20on%20the%20ability%20of%20a%20trained%20model%20to%20respond%20to%20queries%20and%20information%20it%20might%20not%20have%20seen%20before%20with%20reasoning%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Microsoft's%20Ignite%20event%20this%20month%2C%20the%20company's%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Ftsarnick%2Fstatus%2F1858974328790151268%3Fs%3D46%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESatya%20Nadella%20said%20that%20instead%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20seeing%20so-called%20AI%20scaling%20laws%20hit%20a%20wall%2C%20he%20was%20seeing%20the%20emergence%20of%20a%20new%20paradigm%20for%20%26quot%3Btest-time%20compute%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20when%20a%20model%20has%20the%20ability%20to%20take%20longer%20to%20respond%20to%20more%20complex%20prompts%20from%20users.%20Nadella%20pointed%20to%20a%20new%20%26quot%3Bthink%20harder%26quot%3B%20feature%20for%20Copilot%20%E2%80%94%20Microsoft's%20AI%20agent%20%E2%80%94%20which%20boosts%20test%20time%20to%20%26quot%3Bsolve%20even%20harder%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAymeric%20Zhuo%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20AI%20startup%20Agemo%2C%20said%20that%20AI%20reasoning%20%26quot%3Bhas%20been%20an%20active%20area%20of%20research%2C%26quot%3B%20particularly%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20industry%20faces%20a%20data%20wall.%26quot%3B%20He%20told%20BI%20that%20improving%20reasoning%20requires%20increasing%20test-time%20or%20inference-time%20compute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20the%20longer%20a%20model%20takes%20to%20process%20a%20dataset%2C%20the%20more%20accurate%20the%20outcomes%20it%20generates.%20Right%20now%2C%20models%20are%20being%20queried%20in%20milliseconds.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20quite%20make%20sense%2C%26quot%3B%20Sivesh%20Sukumar%2C%20an%20investor%20at%20investment%20firm%20Balderton%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20think%20about%20how%20the%20human%20brain%20works%2C%20even%20the%20smartest%20people%20take%20time%20to%20come%20up%20with%20solutions%20to%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%2C%20OpenAI%20released%20a%20new%20model%2C%20o1%2C%20which%20tries%20to%20%26quot%3Bthink%26quot%3B%20about%20an%20issue%20before%20responding.%20One%20OpenAI%20employee%2C%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20%26quot%3Breasoning%20from%20first%20principles%26quot%3B%20is%20not%20the%20forte%20of%20LLMs%20as%20they%20work%20based%20on%20%26quot%3Ba%20statistical%20probability%20of%20which%20words%20come%20next%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20if%20we%20%26quot%3Bwant%20them%20to%20think%20and%20solve%20novel%20problem%20areas%2C%20they%20have%20to%20reason.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENoam%20Brown%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20OpenAI%2C%20thinks%20the%20impact%20of%20a%20model%20with%20greater%20reasoning%20capabilities%20can%20be%20extraordinary.%20%26quot%3BIt%20turned%20out%20that%20having%20a%20bot%20think%20for%20just%2020%20seconds%20in%20a%20hand%20of%20poker%20got%20the%20same%20boosting%20performance%20as%20scaling%20up%20the%20model%20by%20100%2C000x%20and%20training%20it%20for%20100%2C000%20times%20longer%2C%26quot%3B%20he%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fventurebeat.com%2Fai%2Fopenai-noam-brown-stuns-ted-ai-conference-20-seconds-of-thinking-worth-100000x-more-data%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20said%20during%20a%20talk%20at%20TED%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20and%20OpenAI%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2250a0fbcb-fd6a-42ac-a924-ee852f127c8b%5C%22%3EThe%20AI%20boom%20meets%20its%20tipping%20point%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20efforts%20give%20researchers%20reasons%20to%20remain%20hopeful%2C%20even%20if%20current%20signs%20point%20to%20a%20slower%20rate%20of%20performance%20leaps.%20As%20a%20separate%20former%20DeepMind%20employee%20who%20worked%20on%20Gemini%20told%20BI%2C%20people%20are%20constantly%20%26quot%3Btrying%20to%20find%20all%20sorts%20of%20different%20kinds%20of%20improvements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20the%20industry%20may%20need%20to%20adjust%20to%20a%20slower%20pace%20of%20improvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20think%20we%20went%20through%20this%20crazy%20period%20of%20the%20models%20getting%20better%20really%20fast%2C%20like%2C%20a%20year%20or%20two%20ago.%20It's%20never%20been%20like%20that%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20DeepMind%20employee%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20the%20rate%20of%20improvement%20has%20been%20as%20fast%20this%20year%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20that's%20like%20some%20slowdown.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELamini's%20Zhou%20echoed%20this%20point.%20Scaling%20laws%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cspan%3Ean%20observation%20that%20AI%20models%20improve%20with%20size%2C%20more%20data%2C%20and%20greater%20computing%20power%20%E2%80%94%3C%2Fspan%3Ework%20on%20a%20logarithmic%20scale%20rather%20than%20a%20linear%20one%2C%20she%20said.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20think%20of%20AI%20advances%20as%20a%20curve%20rather%20than%20a%20straight%20upward%20line%20on%20a%20graph.%20That%20makes%20development%20far%20more%20expensive%20%26quot%3Bthan%20we'd%20expect%20for%20the%20next%20substantive%20step%20in%20this%20technology%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhou%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThat's%20why%20I%20think%20our%20expectations%20are%20just%20not%20going%20to%20be%20met%20at%20the%20timeline%20we%20want%2C%20but%20also%20why%20we'll%20be%20more%20surprised%20by%20capabilities%20when%20they%20do%20appear.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222255%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon%20Web%20Services%20(AWS)%20CEO%20Adam%20Selipsky%20speaks%20with%20Anthropic%20CEO%20and%20co-founder%20Dario%20Amodei%20during%20a%202023%20conference.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66098ecd16bde8d4ead3eb84%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon%20Web%20Services%20CEO%20Adam%20Selipsky%20speaks%20with%20Anthropic%20CEO%20Dario%20Amodei%20during%20a%202023%20conference.%3Cp%3ENoah%20Berger%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20will%20also%20need%20to%20consider%20how%20much%20more%20expensive%20it%20will%20be%20to%20create%20the%20next%20versions%20of%20their%20highly%20prized%20models.%20According%20to%20Anthropic's%20Amodei%2C%20a%20training%20run%20in%20the%20future%20could%20one%20day%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-ceo-cost-10-billion-train-ai-years-language-model-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20%24100%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20costs%20include%20GPUs%2C%20energy%20needs%2C%20and%20data%20processing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20investors%20and%20customers%20are%20willing%20to%20wait%20around%20longer%20for%20the%20superintelligence%20they've%20been%20promised%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ai-artificial-intelligence-bet-doubts-marc-benioff-satya-nadella-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIssues%20with%20Microsoft's%20Copilot%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20are%20leading%20some%20customers%20to%20wonder%20if%20the%20much-hyped%20tool%20is%20worth%20the%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20AI%20leaders%20maintain%20that%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20levers%20to%20pull%20%E2%80%94%20from%20new%20data%20sources%20to%20a%20focus%20on%20inference%20%E2%80%94%20to%20ensure%20models%20continue%20improving.%20Investors%20and%20customers%20just%20might%20have%20to%20be%20prepared%20for%20them%20to%20come%20at%20a%20slower%20pace%20compared%20to%20the%20breakneck%20pace%20set%20by%20OpenAI%20when%20it%20launched%20ChatGPT%20two%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBigger%20problems%20lie%20ahead%20if%20they%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgenerative-ai-wall-scaling-laws-training-data-chatgpt-gemini-claude-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732698002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673e124cede4eeae39289e10%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgenerative-ai-wall-scaling-laws-training-data-chatgpt-gemini-claude-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI%20labs%20racing%20to%20surpass%20human%20intelligence%20have%20become%20the%20subject%20of%20reports%20that%20challenges%20are%20getting%20between%20their%20models%20and%20their%20mission.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hchowdhury%40insider.com%20(Hasan%20Chowdhury%2CRiddhi%20Kanetkar%2CBeatrice%20Nolan%2CHugh%20Langley)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgenerative-ai-wall-scaling-laws-training-data-chatgpt-gemini-claude-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20an%20F-35%20funding%20fight%2C%20Musk%20will%20need%20to%20win%20over%20a%20skeptical%20Congress%20and%20Trump%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221913%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20US%20F-35%20in%20flight.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67464cbdfa0140cdd565bcca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221275%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20F-35%20in%20flight.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Senior%20Airman%20Jack%20Rodgers%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EElon%20Musk%20sharply%20criticized%20the%20F-35%20stealth%20jet%20and%20its%20builder%2C%20Lockheed%20Martin.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMusk%20could%20target%20the%20expensive%20program%20as%20part%20of%20his%20efforts%20to%20cut%20federal%20spending%20under%20Trump.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECongress%20has%20historically%20valued%20the%20stealth%20fighter%20flown%20by%20three%20military%20branches%20despite%20its%20problems.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20weeks%20after%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20tasked%20Elon%20Musk%20with%20cutting%20government%20spending%2C%20the%20SpaceX%20CEO%20criticized%20the%20Pentagon's%20most%20expensive%20weapons%20program%3A%20the%20F-35.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20called%20the%20jet's%20design%20%26quot%3Bshit%26quot%3B%20and%20derided%20the%20%26quot%3B